# Conventional Commits

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) for every commit message in this project.

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **type**: required — what kind of change this is
- **scope**: optional — affected area (e.g. `auth`, `lista-dia`, `pwa`)
- **description**: required — imperative, lowercase, no trailing period, max ~72 chars
- **body**: optional — explain the why, not the what
- **footer**: optional — breaking changes, issue refs (`Closes #123`)

## Allowed types

| Type | Use when |
|------|----------|
| `feat` | New feature or user-visible capability |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code change without fixing a bug or adding a feature |
| `style` | Formatting, whitespace, semicolons (no logic change) |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `build` | Build system, dependencies, CI |
| `ci` | CI/CD configuration |
| `chore` | Maintenance, tooling, non-production code |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `revert` | Reverts a previous commit |

## Rules

- Write the subject in **imperative mood**: `add auth gate`, not `added auth gate`
- Keep the subject concise; put detail in the body if needed
- Use `!` after type/scope for breaking changes: `feat(api)!: remove legacy endpoint`
- Match the repository's existing commit style when in doubt

## Examples

```
feat(pwa): add service worker update toast on deploy
```

```
fix(auth): wait for firebase session before route redirect
```

```
refactor(lista-dia): replace invisible selects with tactile status cells
```

```
chore(deps): add framer-motion for ipad microinteractions
```

## Do not

- Use vague messages: `update files`, `wip`, `fixes`
- Mix unrelated changes in one commit
- Commit secrets (`.env`, credentials)
